cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a framework for adaptive and non-adaptive statistical compressive sensing, which involves statistical models and optimal task-specific sensing protocols. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, cs.IT is the most likely category since the paper heavily relies on information theory. The other categories are also likely since the paper deals with machine learning, computer vision, and multimedia applications.
